<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFF33FECE24A7CB03" authorityName="I. D. Rai &amp; B. S. Adhikari" authorityYear="2012" box="[151,396,304,327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rawatii">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFF33FECE24A7CB03" box="[151,396,304,327]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Rhododendron rawatii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFDA8FECE260ACB03" authority="Hooker (1851" authorityName="Hooker" authorityYear="1851" box="[524,801,304,327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFDA8FECE2751CB03" box="[524,634,304,327]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. fulgens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="30594B1C63728A7DFD20FECE260ACB03" author="Hooker, J. D." box="[644,801,304,327]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" pagination="21 - 30" refId="ref3506" refString="Hooker, J. D. (1851) The Rhododendrons of Sikkim-Himalaya 3. Reeve, Benham &amp; Reeve, London, t. 21 - 30." type="book chapter" year="1851">Hooker (1851</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: t. 25) in habit and having peeling bark, glabrous young shoots and shining mature leaves but differs in the abaxial surface of leaves with fascicled cottony hairs in between the lateral veins, a bright pink, not shiny corolla and a large globose calyx with hairy margins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
