<paragraph id="547736ED63728A7DFF33FDE8205BCE30" blockId="2.[151,1436,534,1991]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">
Shrub to small tree up to 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFE64FDE82728C874" box="[448,515,534,560]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="4.5">4.5 m</quantity>
tall; bark thin, papery, peeling, reddish–white. Leaves mostly clustering at the ends of branches; petiole glabrous, 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFDE1FDC327EDC813" box="[581,710,573,599]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="20.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="15.0">15–25 mm</quantity>
long; lamina infolded towards abaxial side from margins at maturity, becoming more convex towards adaxial surface, 122–196 × 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFC6BFD9A217AC83A" box="[975,1105,612,638]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="7.9" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="62.5" valueMax="79.0" valueMin="46.0">46–79 mm</quantity>
, leathery, elliptic to ellipticoblong, base rounded to cordate, apex mucronate, margin entire; adaxial surface green and shiny, abaxial surface with sparsely distributed fascicled white to brown cottony hairs in between lateral veins, becoming more or less glabrous at maturity (1 year); veins conspicuous, lateral veins in 30–44 pairs. Inflorescence terminal, rachis 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFEFEFD0024F0C95C" box="[346,475,766,792]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="16.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="13.0">13–20 mm</quantity>
long, flowers 13–16, loosely arranged; pedicel glabrous, 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFB30FD00202DC95C" box="[1172,1286,766,792]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="13.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="6.0">6–13 mm</quantity>
long; bracts elliptical, convex adaxial surface, apex cuspidate; bracteoles 2, hairy; sepals 5, 2.1–5.6 × 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFB5BFCDB20BCC97B" box="[1279,1431,805,831]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="3.65" valueMax="4.6" valueMin="2.7">2.7–4.6 mm</quantity>
, membranous, globose, pink, margins ciliate with weak hairs; petals 5, tube open-campanulate, 37–49 × 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFAF7FCB225EEC9C8" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" metricValueMax="5.9" metricValueMin="4.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="53.0" valueMax="59.0" valueMin="47.0">47–59 mm</quantity>
(tube length × width at throat), bright pink, not shiny, glabrous, notched, margins entire, with dark pink to brown spots in the corolla tube, well-marked nectar pouches at base of each petal; stamens 10, unequal, 9–19 to 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFF10FC3E2419C99E" box="[180,306,960,986]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="26.5" valueMax="32.0" valueMin="21.0">21–32 mm</quantity>
long (smallest and longest), filaments pubescent at base, white; ovary cylindric, glabrous, green, 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFF33FC1825D2CE44" box="[151,249,998,1024]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
long at the time of flowering; style glabrous, 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFCBFFC1826B1CE44" box="[795,922,998,1024]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="26.0" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="24.0">24–28 mm</quantity>
long, slightly shorter than the corolla tube, persistent; stigma capitate, green, 5-lobed. Capsule 17–28 × 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFCCBFBF326FECE63" box="[879,981,1037,1063]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
, slightly curved at maturity, glabrous, dehiscing from the tip of capsule, placenta remaining attached to central axis after dehiscence; seeds numerous and minute, 1.5–2.5 × 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFDBFFBA42781CE30" box="[539,682,1114,1140]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.5 mm</quantity>
, tailed, tail up to 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFCD1FBA426CBCE30" box="[885,992,1114,1140]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
, compressed and brown in colour.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CD2656663728A7DFF62FB7E2063CD83" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="547736ED63728A7DFF62FB7E2716CE86" blockId="2.[151,1436,534,1991]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFF62FB7E247CCEDE" bold="true" box="[198,343,1152,1178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFDADFB7F2775CEDE" authorityName="I. D. Rai &amp; B. S. Adhikari" authorityYear="2012" box="[521,606,1153,1178]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rawatii">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFDADFB7F2775CEDE" box="[521,606,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">rawatii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
acknowledges Prof. Gopal Singh Rawat, one of the leading phytotaxonomists and ecologists of 
<collectingCountry id="2CDF767D63728A7DFE5EFB562711CE86" box="[506,570,1192,1218]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="547736ED63728A7DFF62FB30244CCF4B" blockId="2.[151,1436,534,1991]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFF62FB302479CEAC" bold="true" box="[198,338,1230,1256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Phenology:</emphasis>
—The flowering period lasts from March to mid-May and capsule dehiscence starts from October onwards.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="547736ED63728A7DFF62FAE526E2CFB3" blockId="2.[151,1436,534,1991]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFF62FAE52441CF71" bold="true" box="[198,362,1307,1333]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Comparison:</emphasis>
—The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFD78FAE2267DCF71" authorityName="Hooker" authorityYear="1851" box="[732,854,1308,1333]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFD78FAE2267DCF71" box="[732,854,1308,1333]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and shares several common characters, such as habit (a small tree to shrub), peeling bark, glabrous young shoots and shining leaves at maturity. The new species differs in many characters as follows: light green abaxial surface of leaf with fascicled cottony hairs in between lateral veins in 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFE1AFA6E271DCFED" authorityName="I. D. Rai &amp; B. S. Adhikari" authorityYear="2012" box="[446,566,1424,1449]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rawatii">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFE1AFA6E271DCFED" box="[446,566,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. rawatii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFD75FA6E2662CFED" authorityName="Hooker" authorityYear="1851" box="[721,841,1424,1449]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFD75FA6E2662CFED" box="[721,841,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the indumentum wholly obliterates the venation. Flowers are dark pink having a globose calyx with hairy margins in 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFC6CFA492114CF94" authorityName="I. D. Rai &amp; B. S. Adhikari" authorityYear="2012" box="[968,1087,1463,1488]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rawatii">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFC6CFA492114CF94" box="[968,1087,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. rawatii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFB73FA492065CF94" authorityName="Hooker" authorityYear="1851" box="[1239,1358,1463,1488]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFB73FA492065CF94" box="[1239,1358,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
petals are bright blood-red, highly polished and shining, the calyx is minute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="547736ED63728A7DFF62F9FD2063CD83" blockId="2.[151,1436,534,1991]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFF62F9FD27AACC59" bold="true" box="[198,641,1539,1565]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">
Study area, forest 
<typeStatus id="8B73884F63728A7DFE0DF9FD24F4CC59" box="[425,479,1539,1565]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
and climate:
</emphasis>
—The study area is located in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="960CF80F63728A7DFBCAF9FA21D5CC5A" box="[1134,1278,1540,1566]" country="India" name="Uttarakhand" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Uttarakhand</collectingRegion>
of the Indian Republic (
<figureCitation id="CCF32A6863728A7DFEB6F9D42471CC00" box="[274,346,1578,1604]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,244,1391,1412]" captionTargetBox="[314,1271,816,1368]" captionTargetId="figure-412@5.[313,1273,815,1369]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Map of India (left lower side) and Uttarakhand state (representing locations of the habitat of R. rawatii recorded (left star type locality at Tungnath in Kedarnath Wildlife Sanctuary, Rudraprayag (R) district and right star enroute Chhipla–Kedar in Pithoragarh (P) district)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066325" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066325/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The species is mainly recorded in the subalpine–timberline ecotone region. The subalpine forests are dominated by 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFE65F9AF2624CC2F" authority="Sm." authorityName="Sm." box="[449,783,1617,1643]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semecarpifolia">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFE65F9AF27F2CC2E" box="[449,729,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Quercus semecarpifolia</emphasis>
Sm.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFCBAF9AF2125CC2F" authority="D. Don" authorityName="D. Don" box="[798,1038,1617,1643]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="utilis">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFCBAF9AF2686CC2E" box="[798,941,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Betula utilis</emphasis>
D. Don
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFBBEF9AF20B7CC2F" authority="(D. Don) Mirb." authorityName="Mirb." baseAuthorityName="D. Don" box="[1050,1436,1617,1643]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spectabilis">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFBBEF9AF21CBCC2E" box="[1050,1248,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Abies spectabilis</emphasis>
(D. Don) Mirb.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFF6DF98624C4CCD5" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1805" box="[201,495,1656,1681]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arboreum">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFF6DF98624C4CCD5" box="[201,495,1656,1681]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Rhododendron arboreum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFD90F986279DCCD5" box="[564,694,1656,1681]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">krummholz</emphasis>
dominated by 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFCC2F98620B3CCD6" authority="Don (1821: 410)" authorityName="Don" authorityPageNumber="410" authorityYear="1821" box="[870,1432,1656,1682]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="campanulatum">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFCC2F98621E2CCD5" box="[870,1225,1656,1681]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">Rhododendron campanulatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="30594B1C63728A7DFB74F98620B3CCD6" author="Don, D." box="[1232,1432,1656,1682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" pagination="407 - 415" refId="ref3268" refString="Don, D. (1821) Descriptions of the several new plants from the Kingdom of Nepaul, taken from specimens preserved in the herbarium of Aylmer Bourke Lambert, Esq, Memoirs of the Wernerian Natural History Society 3: 407 - 415." type="journal article" year="1821">Don (1821: 410)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Six species of 
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFEE6F96124DECCFC" box="[322,501,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFEE6F96124D9CCFC" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[322,498,1695,1720]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Rhododendron</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
viz. 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFD95F96127EFCCFC" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1805" box="[561,708,1695,1720]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arboreum">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFD95F96127EFCCFC" box="[561,708,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. arboreum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFD77F9612192CCFC" authority="Wallich ex Don (1834: 844)" authorityName="Don" authorityPageNumber="844" authorityYear="1834" box="[723,1209,1694,1720]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barbatum">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFD77F961264DCCFC" box="[723,870,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. barbatum</emphasis>
Wallich ex 
<bibRefCitation id="30594B1C63728A7DFC56F9602192CCFC" author="Don, G." box="[1010,1209,1694,1720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" refId="ref3314" refString="Don, G. (1834) A General History of the Dichlamydeous Plants 3. J. G. &amp; F. Rivington, London, 867 pp." type="book" year="1834">Don (1834: 844)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFB61F96120BECCFC" authorityName="Don" authorityYear="1821" box="[1221,1429,1695,1720]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="campanulatum">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFB61F96120BECCFC" box="[1221,1429,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. campanulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFF33F93B2739CC9B" authority="Don (1821: 409)" authorityName="Don" authorityPageNumber="409" authorityYear="1821" box="[151,530,1733,1759]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anthopogon">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFF33F93B246FCC9A" box="[151,324,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. anthopogon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="30594B1C63728A7DFEE8F93B2739CC9B" author="Don, D." box="[332,530,1733,1759]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" pagination="407 - 415" refId="ref3268" refString="Don, D. (1821) Descriptions of the several new plants from the Kingdom of Nepaul, taken from specimens preserved in the herbarium of Aylmer Bourke Lambert, Esq, Memoirs of the Wernerian Natural History Society 3: 407 - 415." type="journal article" year="1821">Don (1821: 409)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFDBBF93B212CCC9B" authority="Wallich ex Don (1834: 845)" authorityName="Don" authorityPageNumber="845" authorityYear="1834" box="[543,1031,1733,1759]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lepidotum">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFDBBF93B279ECC9A" box="[543,693,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. lepidotum</emphasis>
Wallich ex 
<bibRefCitation id="30594B1C63728A7DFCE7F93B212CCC9B" author="Don, G." box="[835,1031,1733,1759]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" refId="ref3314" refString="Don, G. (1834) A General History of the Dichlamydeous Plants 3. J. G. &amp; F. Rivington, London, 867 pp." type="book" year="1834">Don (1834: 845)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="93C84D6E63728A7DFBE6F93B20AFCC9B" authority="Hooker (1851: 26" authorityName="Hooker" authorityYear="1851" box="[1090,1412,1733,1759]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nivale">
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFBE6F93B2181CC9A" box="[1090,1194,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">R. nivale</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="30594B1C63728A7DFB16F93B20AFCC9B" author="Hooker, J. D." box="[1202,1412,1733,1759]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" pagination="21 - 30" refId="ref3506" refString="Hooker, J. D. (1851) The Rhododendrons of Sikkim-Himalaya 3. Reeve, Benham &amp; Reeve, London, t. 21 - 30." type="book chapter" year="1851">Hooker (1851: 26</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
b) have been reported from the Western Himalaya. The climatic data were recorded for 3 years during 2008–2010 at Tungnath area (
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFE50F8EC2765CD68" box="[500,590,1810,1836]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="3300.0">3300 m</quantity>
a.s.l.) in Kedarnath WS (
<typeStatus id="8B73884F63728A7DFCD2F8EC2681CD68" box="[886,938,1810,1836]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
locality), and the climate of the region has three prominent seasons: long winter (October to April), short dry summer (May to June) and rainy season (July to September). The mean annual temperature ranged between -8.9°C (January) and +25.6°C (May) with an annual average of 6.6±0.7°C. The annual precipitation was 2410± 
<quantity id="93309B0863728A7DFC7DF878216BCDE4" box="[985,1088,1926,1952]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.32" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="432.0">432 mm</quantity>
, of which 89% was received during June–September. The area remains snow-bound for 85±28 days per year (
<bibRefCitation id="30594B1C63728A7DFBEDF8532010CD83" author="Adhikari, B. S. &amp; Rawat, G. S. &amp; Rai, I. D. &amp; Bhattacharyya, S. &amp; Bharati, R. R." box="[1097,1339,1965,1991]" pageId="2" pageNumber="12" refId="ref3022" refString="Adhikari, B. S., Rawat, G. S., Rai, I. D., Bhattacharyya, S. &amp; Bharati, R. R. (2011) Ecological assessment of timberline ecotone in Western Himalaya with special reference to climate change and anthropogenic pressures. IV Annual report. Wildlife Institute of India, Dehradun, 29 pp." type="book" year="2011">
Adhikari 
<emphasis id="66BCEAFF63728A7DFB1FF85321DECD82" box="[1211,1269,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
